# AeroHealth Forecast Environment Variables

# No API keys required for basic functionality!
# Open-Meteo API is free and doesn't require authentication.

# ============================================
# NASA FIRMS API Configuration
# ============================================
# NASA FIRMS (Fire Information for Resource Management System)
# Provides real-time wildfire detection data from satellites
#
# HOW TO GET YOUR API KEY:
# 1. Visit: https://firms.modaps.eosdis.nasa.gov/api/area/
# 2. Click "Request a MAP_KEY"
# 3. Fill out the form with your email and intended use
# 4. Verify your email address
# 5. Receive your MAP_KEY via email (usually within minutes)
# 6. Copy your MAP_KEY and paste it below
#
# SETUP:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local
# 2. Replace "your_map_key_here" with your actual MAP_KEY
# 3. Restart your development server
#
# NOTE: If not configured, the app will use mock wildfire data
NASA_FIRMS_API_KEY=your_map_key_here

# ============================================
# Other API Keys (Optional)
# ============================================
# The following APIs are used but don't require API keys:
# - Open-Meteo API (air quality, weather, pollen data)
# - OpenStreetMap Overpass API (highways, industrial areas)
#
# If you want to add additional data sources, you can add them here:
# OPENAQ_API_KEY=your_openaq_key_here
# WEATHERAPI_KEY=your_weatherapi_key_here

# Optional: OpenAQ API Key (for enhanced air quality data)
# Get your free API key at: https://openaq.org/
OPENAQ_API_KEY=your_api_key_here

# If you want to add additional API sources in the future, add them here:
# OPENWEATHER_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
# IQAIR_API_KEY=your_api_key_here

